1
00:00:00,767 --> 00:00:03,567
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:03,700 --> 00:00:04,700
How long will it take
before she goes back

3
00:00:04,833 --> 00:00:06,167
to how she was before?

4
00:00:06,300 --> 00:00:07,533
It can take weeks,

5
00:00:07,667 --> 00:00:09,133
it could also take months...

6
00:00:09,267 --> 00:00:10,600
or even years.

7
00:00:10,733 --> 00:00:12,800
I do not want to stay like this
for so long.

8
00:00:12,933 --> 00:00:14,467
I cannot handle it.

9
00:00:14,600 --> 00:00:17,500
Edward, you have the nerve
to show up here.

10
00:00:17,633 --> 00:00:19,967
Did you gain anything
by letting Aldrin use you?

11
00:00:20,100 --> 00:00:23,067
If only you had treated me
like a child even once,

12
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:24,800
then I would not have turned
against you.

13
00:00:24,933 --> 00:00:25,933
Do not throw that in my face.

14
00:00:26,067 --> 00:00:27,300
There is still a lot
you do not know.

15
00:00:27,433 --> 00:00:30,300
What did we ever do to you
for you to destroy us?

16
00:00:30,433 --> 00:00:33,433
Your family did nothing.
But you? You owe me.

17
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:34,700
I need answers, Mom.

18
00:00:34,833 --> 00:00:36,167
Mom, what is it
that I do not know?

19
00:00:36,300 --> 00:00:37,633
Is there no other reason

20
00:00:37,767 --> 00:00:39,300
why he would be
this angry with me?

21
00:00:39,433 --> 00:00:44,400
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

22
00:01:26,067 --> 00:01:27,200
- [SOBBING]
- Thea, please.

23
00:01:27,333 --> 00:01:29,467
Losing control right now
will not help.

24
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:32,633
Let us find out everything first
before we react like this.

25
00:01:32,767 --> 00:01:34,233
What happened, Doctor?

26
00:01:34,367 --> 00:01:36,633
The healing process
can take some time.

27
00:01:36,767 --> 00:01:40,133
Ashley's nerves
are still recovering.

28
00:01:42,567 --> 00:01:46,533
Doctor, can therapy help this?

29
00:01:46,667 --> 00:01:47,700
It is part of the process.

30
00:01:47,833 --> 00:01:49,300
It is necessary.

31
00:01:49,433 --> 00:01:52,600
But how long before she returns
to normal?

32
00:01:52,733 --> 00:01:57,767
It can take some weeks, months,

33
00:01:57,900 --> 00:01:59,633
or even years.

34
00:02:02,533 --> 00:02:03,700
One year?

35
00:02:04,767 --> 00:02:07,100
One year that I cannot walk?

36
00:02:07,233 --> 00:02:09,400
[SOBBING]

37
00:02:10,633 --> 00:02:11,900
But, Mom, didn't you say

38
00:02:12,033 --> 00:02:14,967
everything would be okay
after this?

39
00:02:17,100 --> 00:02:19,233
I do not want to stay like this.

40
00:02:19,367 --> 00:02:21,933
I cannot handle it.

41
00:02:22,067 --> 00:02:24,167
[SOBBING]

42
00:02:24,300 --> 00:02:27,267
There are still so many things
I want to do.

43
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:28,300
[SOBBING]

44
00:02:28,433 --> 00:02:31,367
How will I go back to school?

45
00:02:31,500 --> 00:02:35,900
How can I do that
if I cannot walk?

46
00:02:36,033 --> 00:02:38,567
[SOBBING]

47
00:02:40,267 --> 00:02:43,033
How am I supposed to do that?

48
00:02:44,133 --> 00:02:48,267
[SOBBING]

49
00:02:57,667 --> 00:03:02,367
- [DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]
- [CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

50
00:03:06,700 --> 00:03:11,533
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

51
00:03:21,733 --> 00:03:23,067
<i> Ladies and gentlemen,</i>

52
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:25,133
<i>let us give a round of applause</i>

53
00:03:25,267 --> 00:03:29,467
<i>for this historic union
for the Asian Business Complex,</i>

54
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:31,300
<i> soon to be the premier hub</i>

55
00:03:31,433 --> 00:03:34,333
<i>for global commerce
in the country.</i>

56
00:03:34,467 --> 00:03:39,233
- [APPLAUDING]
- [MUSIC CONTINUES]

57
00:03:55,433 --> 00:03:58,833
[APPLAUDING]

58
00:04:03,633 --> 00:04:06,100
Do not think you have
already won.

59
00:04:06,233 --> 00:04:08,400
I will not let you ruin
the company

60
00:04:08,533 --> 00:04:10,733
that my dad worked hard for.

61
00:04:10,867 --> 00:04:13,100
And I will make sure

62
00:04:13,233 --> 00:04:15,567
that I take it back from you.

63
00:04:15,700 --> 00:04:17,933
Do not be like that, Paolo.

64
00:04:18,067 --> 00:04:19,700
I know this is all new to you

65
00:04:19,833 --> 00:04:21,667
because you are used
to winning.

66
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:23,933
But get used to it.

67
00:04:24,067 --> 00:04:25,800
I am just getting started.

68
00:04:25,933 --> 00:04:29,733
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

69
00:04:29,900 --> 00:04:33,467
[APPLAUDING]

70
00:04:43,267 --> 00:04:45,400
You do not need to feed me.

71
00:04:48,433 --> 00:04:50,300
Only my legs cannot move,

72
00:04:51,333 --> 00:04:52,700
not my hands.

73
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:55,900
I am just doing
my boyfriend duties.

74
00:04:57,333 --> 00:04:59,567
Hey, I am just joking.

75
00:04:59,700 --> 00:05:01,400
You might get annoyed.

76
00:05:01,567 --> 00:05:04,767
Stop wasting your time, Xander.

77
00:05:06,533 --> 00:05:08,533
I do not need your pity.

78
00:05:11,567 --> 00:05:13,500
I am not here out of pity.

79
00:05:14,700 --> 00:05:16,933
I am doing this
because I like you.

80
00:05:19,133 --> 00:05:21,067
Do you really want
to have a girlfriend

81
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:23,333
who will be in a wheelchair
forever?

82
00:05:23,467 --> 00:05:24,667
Don't say that.

83
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:25,867
You still have therapy.

84
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:27,800
- You might walk again.
- That is not certain.

85
00:05:30,267 --> 00:05:32,200
That is why I do not want
to expect anything.

86
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:36,033
Because I might just
end up heartbroken.

87
00:05:37,367 --> 00:05:40,300
- But, Ash...
- Stop pushing it, Xander.

88
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:44,900
Leave now.

89
00:05:48,100 --> 00:05:50,033
Just leave.

90
00:05:50,167 --> 00:05:51,467
Leave me alone.

91
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:55,367
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

92
00:06:09,467 --> 00:06:12,867
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

93
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:16,133
[SOBBING]

94
00:06:26,567 --> 00:06:27,700
Paolo already left.

95
00:06:27,833 --> 00:06:29,200
He has a meeting
with some suppliers.

96
00:06:29,333 --> 00:06:30,767
Mom is talking to someone.

97
00:06:30,900 --> 00:06:32,867
But we are on our way there.

98
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,933
Yes, Marj. I am just
at the back,

99
00:06:35,067 --> 00:06:37,067
I am heading
to the parking area.

100
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:38,767
- Okay, see you.
- Edward.

101
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:44,433
You have the nerve
to show up here.

102
00:06:46,167 --> 00:06:48,400
I did not come here for you.

103
00:06:48,533 --> 00:06:50,100
I am here to thank
Paolo and Marj

104
00:06:50,233 --> 00:06:52,033
for helping me
with Ashley's operation.

105
00:06:52,167 --> 00:06:53,833
[HUFFS]

106
00:06:53,967 --> 00:06:55,567
What you really mean is...

107
00:06:55,700 --> 00:06:57,400
you came here to gloat.

108
00:06:58,500 --> 00:07:01,000
Do you think you already
got revenge?

109
00:07:01,133 --> 00:07:02,400
Why?

110
00:07:02,533 --> 00:07:05,533
Did you gain anything
by letting Aldrin use you?

111
00:07:05,667 --> 00:07:07,033
Why, Dad?

112
00:07:07,167 --> 00:07:08,667
Did you not use me too?

113
00:07:09,967 --> 00:07:11,100
What the hell
are you talking about?

114
00:07:11,233 --> 00:07:12,433
All my life,

115
00:07:12,567 --> 00:07:16,400
you only used me as decoration
to polish your image.

116
00:07:16,567 --> 00:07:18,100
To make you look like
a good father

117
00:07:18,233 --> 00:07:20,000
and our family look perfect.

118
00:07:23,033 --> 00:07:25,567
If I had known
you would betray me,

119
00:07:26,933 --> 00:07:29,233
I should have kicked you out
long ago!

120
00:07:29,367 --> 00:07:31,467
You should have.

121
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:32,700
Especially,

122
00:07:32,833 --> 00:07:37,167
I have long been tired of you
being a worthless father!

123
00:07:37,300 --> 00:07:38,633
Like the company...

124
00:07:38,767 --> 00:07:41,400
they are also sick of you!

125
00:07:41,533 --> 00:07:42,467
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

126
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:44,533
- [THUDS]
- [GRUNTS]

127
00:07:48,333 --> 00:07:49,167
Greg!

128
00:07:51,167 --> 00:07:52,833
- Edward!
- What is wrong with you?

129
00:07:53,867 --> 00:07:58,667
If only you had treated me
like a child even once,

130
00:07:58,800 --> 00:08:00,833
I would not have turned
against you.

131
00:08:00,967 --> 00:08:02,167
Shut your mouth!

132
00:08:03,300 --> 00:08:05,033
Do not throw that in my face.

133
00:08:05,167 --> 00:08:06,667
There is still a lot
you do not know!

134
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:09,067
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

135
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:12,300
Edward, stop engaging with him.

136
00:08:12,433 --> 00:08:13,400
Come on!

137
00:08:17,167 --> 00:08:18,400
Greg!

138
00:08:18,533 --> 00:08:19,867
Come here.

139
00:08:29,133 --> 00:08:31,100
I am done, Greg.

140
00:08:32,133 --> 00:08:33,967
I used to think
that if I stayed quiet

141
00:08:34,100 --> 00:08:35,733
and followed everything
you wanted,

142
00:08:35,867 --> 00:08:36,867
you would change.

143
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:38,033
But you did not.

144
00:08:38,167 --> 00:08:39,767
You only got worse.

145
00:08:39,900 --> 00:08:43,000
I can no longer accept
what you are doing to Edward.

146
00:08:43,133 --> 00:08:44,167
He already has so many problems,

147
00:08:44,300 --> 00:08:46,467
and you are still
pushing him down.

148
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:49,267
He was the one
who challenged me first.

149
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:51,200
Can you blame him?

150
00:08:51,333 --> 00:08:53,967
You are the real monster
of this family.

151
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:55,900
And I am sick of it!

152
00:08:57,133 --> 00:08:59,067
And you still have the nerve
to boast?

153
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:01,167
After what you did?

154
00:09:01,300 --> 00:09:03,133
You know why I am like this
toward Edward.

155
00:09:03,267 --> 00:09:04,400
I know.

156
00:09:04,533 --> 00:09:07,233
And until now,
you are still wrong.

157
00:09:07,367 --> 00:09:10,033
And as long as you stand
by your lies,

158
00:09:10,167 --> 00:09:12,767
my view of him
will never change, Regina.

159
00:09:12,900 --> 00:09:17,200
And never will I accept Edward
because he is not my real child!

160
00:09:17,333 --> 00:09:22,000
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

161
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:31,800
You know that is not true.

162
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:35,100
Edward is your own
flesh and blood.

163
00:09:35,233 --> 00:09:38,667
Do you think you are
the only one hurting here?

164
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,800
I am hurting even more

165
00:09:41,933 --> 00:09:45,067
because every time
I see your child's face,

166
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:46,567
all I remember...

167
00:09:48,433 --> 00:09:49,867
is your betrayal.

168
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:52,833
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

169
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:04,333
<i>- Greg!
- Regina.</i>

170
00:10:05,433 --> 00:10:06,833
<i>- Greg!
- Walter?</i>

171
00:10:06,967 --> 00:10:08,733
<i>Bro, wait, I can explain, okay?</i>

172
00:10:08,867 --> 00:10:09,800
<i>I will kill you!
[THUDS]</i>

173
00:10:09,933 --> 00:10:11,633
<i> [CLAMORING]</i>

174
00:10:11,767 --> 00:10:12,833
<i>- [THUDDING]
- [GRUNTING]</i>

175
00:10:12,967 --> 00:10:14,400
<i>- Stop it!
- Bro, wait.</i>

176
00:10:14,533 --> 00:10:15,833
<i> I thought you were my friend.</i>

177
00:10:15,967 --> 00:10:17,333
<i> [THUDS]</i>

178
00:10:22,633 --> 00:10:24,400
<i> Greg, stop it!</i>

179
00:10:24,533 --> 00:10:25,633
<i> [SLAPS]</i>

180
00:10:27,900 --> 00:10:30,633
<i>So, he's the guy
you're cheating with?</i>

181
00:10:30,767 --> 00:10:32,400
<i>You were making a fool out of me
behind my back!</i>

182
00:10:32,533 --> 00:10:34,100
<i> Greg, I am hurt.</i>

183
00:10:34,233 --> 00:10:35,767
<i> You will regret this.</i>

184
00:10:35,933 --> 00:10:38,500
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

185
00:10:38,633 --> 00:10:40,200
<i> No.</i>

186
00:10:40,333 --> 00:10:42,467
<i> I will never regret this.</i>

187
00:10:43,767 --> 00:10:45,033
<i> You know why?</i>

188
00:10:46,400 --> 00:10:49,467
<i>Because I have been miserable
under your control.</i>

189
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:53,600
<i>You think I did not know
about all your affairs?</i>

190
00:10:53,733 --> 00:10:55,033
<i> You chose him?</i>

191
00:10:58,400 --> 00:10:59,833
<i> He's my business partner!</i>

192
00:10:59,967 --> 00:11:01,033
<i> You are disgusting!</i>

193
00:11:02,067 --> 00:11:04,900
<i> Despite all your cheating,</i>

194
00:11:05,033 --> 00:11:07,833
<i>he was the only one
who respected me.</i>

195
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:09,300
<i> Unlike you.</i>

196
00:11:10,867 --> 00:11:12,433
<i> What?</i>

197
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:14,933
<i> Remember this,</i>

198
00:11:15,967 --> 00:11:18,000
<i> nobody cheats on me.</i>

199
00:11:18,133 --> 00:11:19,267
<i> Believe me.</i>

200
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:23,967
<i>I will make your life miserable
from now on.</i>

201
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:25,767
<i> You are ungrateful!</i>

202
00:11:25,900 --> 00:11:27,500
<i> [GRUMBLES]</i>

203
00:11:27,633 --> 00:11:29,133
<i> [WHIMPERS]</i>

204
00:11:29,267 --> 00:11:31,267
<i> Stop! Please, Greg!</i>

205
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:35,333
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

206
00:11:43,567 --> 00:11:45,533
<i> Go to sleep, baby.</i>

207
00:11:47,167 --> 00:11:48,833
<i>- Go to sleep.
- [BABY COOING]</i>

208
00:11:48,967 --> 00:11:53,100
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

209
00:12:07,433 --> 00:12:11,300
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

210
00:12:12,900 --> 00:12:14,533
<i> What now, Regina?</i>

211
00:12:14,700 --> 00:12:15,600
<i> Are you going to admit it now?</i>

212
00:12:17,800 --> 00:12:19,567
<i>That Walter
is the child's father?</i>

213
00:12:22,433 --> 00:12:25,933
<i>Greg, did I not already
tell you?</i>

214
00:12:27,067 --> 00:12:28,600
<i>We already ended
our relationship</i>

215
00:12:28,733 --> 00:12:30,667
<i> when you caught us.</i>

216
00:12:32,667 --> 00:12:34,500
<i> Edward is your child.</i>

217
00:12:37,100 --> 00:12:38,067
<i> Here.</i>

218
00:12:40,400 --> 00:12:41,400
<i> Look at this.</i>

219
00:12:41,533 --> 00:12:44,933
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

220
00:12:48,900 --> 00:12:51,567
<i>Do you think I will believe
that piece of paper?</i>

221
00:12:51,700 --> 00:12:54,933
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

222
00:12:55,067 --> 00:12:58,000
<i>How can I be sure that
this DNA test is real?</i>

223
00:12:58,133 --> 00:12:59,967
<i> Do you know this can be faked?</i>

224
00:13:00,100 --> 00:13:03,233
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

225
00:13:21,100 --> 00:13:23,100
I may have cheated,

226
00:13:23,233 --> 00:13:26,833
but I did not lie
that Edward is your child!

227
00:13:26,967 --> 00:13:29,400
I still do not believe you.

228
00:13:29,533 --> 00:13:34,467
I will never be fooled by you
or anyone else ever again!

229
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:35,800
Ever again!

230
00:13:35,933 --> 00:13:37,100
Dad, stop it!

231
00:13:37,233 --> 00:13:38,900
Stop it, you are hurting mom!

232
00:13:39,033 --> 00:13:40,067
Stop it!

233
00:13:41,467 --> 00:13:42,500
Dad.

234
00:13:47,433 --> 00:13:49,933
What he is saying is not true.

235
00:13:51,067 --> 00:13:53,800
Edward is Greg's child.

236
00:13:53,933 --> 00:13:56,533
He is a Torrecampo.

237
00:13:56,700 --> 00:14:01,267
Mom, Edward deserves to know
the truth.

238
00:14:01,400 --> 00:14:05,200
So he can understand why his
father treats him that way.

239
00:14:05,333 --> 00:14:06,567
No.

240
00:14:06,700 --> 00:14:09,200
You cannot tell my sons
about this.

241
00:14:09,333 --> 00:14:11,100
I do not want to confuse
Edward even more.

242
00:14:11,233 --> 00:14:13,067
He is going through so much.

243
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:14,800
- But, Mom...
- No, no, no.

244
00:14:14,933 --> 00:14:17,033
Promise me.

245
00:14:17,167 --> 00:14:18,767
Promise me, Marj.

246
00:14:21,233 --> 00:14:22,333
Promise me.

247
00:14:22,467 --> 00:14:26,200
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

248
00:14:45,667 --> 00:14:46,767
Marj.

249
00:14:51,667 --> 00:14:52,600
[SIGHS]

250
00:14:52,733 --> 00:14:56,333
I am sorry about what happened.

251
00:14:56,467 --> 00:14:59,933
I think you should not apologize
to me.

252
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,567
To my mom.

253
00:15:02,733 --> 00:15:04,067
No, no, no.

254
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:06,433
I am not talking about tonight.

255
00:15:06,567 --> 00:15:09,233
I am talking about
helping Thea and Paolo

256
00:15:09,367 --> 00:15:11,600
hide their secret.

257
00:15:11,733 --> 00:15:13,133
Especially from you.

258
00:15:16,633 --> 00:15:19,600
We were both victims
of our spouses.

259
00:15:19,733 --> 00:15:24,933
We both endured the consequences
of their infidelity.

260
00:15:26,167 --> 00:15:29,233
Why do you refuse
to believe mom

261
00:15:29,367 --> 00:15:31,600
that Edward is his child?

262
00:15:31,733 --> 00:15:34,533
When Paolo denied that Ashley
was his child,

263
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:38,233
even with the timeline
of the affair,

264
00:15:38,367 --> 00:15:39,833
would you believe him?

265
00:15:45,167 --> 00:15:48,567
I know exactly how it feels
to be humiliated.

266
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:51,233
That is why...

267
00:15:51,367 --> 00:15:53,633
I should not have
hidden the truth.

268
00:15:54,733 --> 00:15:55,900
But you know me.

269
00:15:57,033 --> 00:16:02,667
I had to keep my name clean
for the sake of the family.

270
00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:06,433
That is why I let Edward
be Ashley's father

271
00:16:07,900 --> 00:16:10,767
and I became Edward's
father figure.

272
00:16:12,567 --> 00:16:14,500
I understand that.

273
00:16:16,833 --> 00:16:19,433
What Paolo did to me
was painful.

274
00:16:19,567 --> 00:16:21,167
That is why I know
what your spouse did to you

275
00:16:21,300 --> 00:16:22,833
was painful too.

276
00:16:24,767 --> 00:16:27,867
But Edward and Ashley,

277
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:29,800
they are innocent.

278
00:16:31,967 --> 00:16:34,033
I accept Ashley

279
00:16:34,167 --> 00:16:38,467
because she has no fault.

280
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:41,067
The same goes for Edward.

281
00:16:42,333 --> 00:16:44,133
Ashley and Edward,

282
00:16:45,167 --> 00:16:47,100
they did nothing wrong.

283
00:16:48,200 --> 00:16:50,633
They were simply born.

284
00:16:50,767 --> 00:16:54,200
[LAUGHS]

285
00:16:54,333 --> 00:16:55,933
You're lying.

286
00:16:56,067 --> 00:16:57,800
You don't want Ashley around.

287
00:16:57,933 --> 00:17:01,367
Why would you want a reminder
of Paolo's betrayal?

288
00:17:03,500 --> 00:17:06,767
You're stupid if you want
that child

289
00:17:06,900 --> 00:17:09,167
beyond her usefulness
for Jasmine's health.

290
00:17:11,900 --> 00:17:14,233
That is not how I see Ashley.

291
00:17:15,333 --> 00:17:19,367
I believe she deserves
to be loved and accepted.

292
00:17:19,500 --> 00:17:20,767
And Edward as well.

293
00:17:21,967 --> 00:17:24,167
We may be going through
similar pain,

294
00:17:24,300 --> 00:17:28,167
but do not assume
that we feel the same way.

295
00:17:31,600 --> 00:17:32,933
Excuse me.

296
00:17:39,300 --> 00:17:42,300
[INTENSE MUSIC PAYING]

297
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:49,767
I am sorry it all came to this.

298
00:17:51,133 --> 00:17:53,333
You do not deserve
what is happening.

299
00:17:57,867 --> 00:17:59,467
Tell that to my father.

300
00:18:01,733 --> 00:18:04,633
Do you remember our conversation
before?

301
00:18:04,767 --> 00:18:06,800
Back when Paolo and I
were not together?

302
00:18:08,600 --> 00:18:10,567
We were just like this
back then.

303
00:18:11,733 --> 00:18:15,100
We could relate to each other.

304
00:18:15,233 --> 00:18:17,767
That is how we became friends

305
00:18:17,900 --> 00:18:21,667
because we talked about
our misfortunes.

306
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:27,333
Are you okay?

307
00:18:27,467 --> 00:18:29,167
Something is bothering me.

308
00:18:30,700 --> 00:18:31,700
What is it?

309
00:18:33,400 --> 00:18:34,867
Dad said something.

310
00:18:36,433 --> 00:18:38,500
He said there is still a lot
I do not know.

311
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:41,100
What could that be?

312
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:47,100
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYiNG]

313
00:18:48,600 --> 00:18:49,867
<i> No.</i>

314
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:52,500
<i>You can't tell my sons
about this.</i>

315
00:18:52,633 --> 00:18:54,567
<i>I don't want to confuse Edward
any further.</i>

316
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:56,400
<i> He's going through so much.</i>

317
00:18:56,567 --> 00:18:58,067
<i>- But, Mom...
- No, no, no.</i>

318
00:18:58,200 --> 00:18:59,333
Promise me.

319
00:19:01,533 --> 00:19:03,233
Whatever it is,
I'm sure it's connected

320
00:19:03,367 --> 00:19:05,933
to how he treated you
your whole life.

321
00:19:08,700 --> 00:19:10,067
You mean,

322
00:19:10,200 --> 00:19:12,367
the reason why he's like that
toward me?

323
00:19:15,367 --> 00:19:19,600
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

324
00:19:24,933 --> 00:19:27,800
[PHONE RINGING]

325
00:19:31,767 --> 00:19:32,800
Hello?

326
00:19:32,933 --> 00:19:35,067
Hello, Miss?

327
00:19:35,200 --> 00:19:37,100
What was that text you sent me?

328
00:19:37,233 --> 00:19:40,267
<i>Why is Ashley also
in the hospital?</i>

329
00:19:40,400 --> 00:19:43,733
She had complications
from donating to Jasmine.

330
00:19:43,867 --> 00:19:46,467
<i> So, now she's sick too.</i>

331
00:19:46,600 --> 00:19:49,000
They say she can't walk.

332
00:19:49,133 --> 00:19:51,433
Those children are so pitiful.

333
00:19:51,567 --> 00:19:54,567
They're paying the price
for their parents' sins.

334
00:19:54,700 --> 00:19:55,767
Oh, dear, Miss.

335
00:19:56,267 --> 00:19:58,700
Things are so chaotic here
at home right now.

336
00:19:58,833 --> 00:20:02,333
Even us, Sir Greg is taking it
out on us.

337
00:20:02,500 --> 00:20:03,500
Why?

338
00:20:03,633 --> 00:20:05,467
Well, Miss,

339
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:11,100
Sir Greg wants us to reveal
where you are.

340
00:20:11,233 --> 00:20:14,133
Even though we're talking
like this,

341
00:20:14,267 --> 00:20:16,900
I honestly still don't know
where you are.

342
00:20:19,133 --> 00:20:20,467
Oh, Weng.

343
00:20:20,600 --> 00:20:23,433
I'm sorry you got dragged
into this.

344
00:20:23,567 --> 00:20:25,767
<i> But, Weng, believe me.</i>

345
00:20:25,900 --> 00:20:26,967
I really didn't do
anything wrong.

346
00:20:27,100 --> 00:20:29,000
I didn't burn the house down.

347
00:20:30,067 --> 00:20:32,867
Of course, Miss, we know that.

348
00:20:34,033 --> 00:20:37,767
<i> But if it wasn't you,</i>

349
00:20:37,933 --> 00:20:39,167
then who could it be?

350
00:20:39,300 --> 00:20:44,067
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

351
00:20:54,033 --> 00:20:55,633
Edward,

352
00:20:55,767 --> 00:20:58,233
you might end up
hospitalized yourself.

353
00:20:59,267 --> 00:21:02,800
Since when did you
start smoking?

354
00:21:02,933 --> 00:21:05,433
- [EXHALES]
- Since Ashley's first surgery.

355
00:21:06,733 --> 00:21:08,500
I've been so stressed.

356
00:21:08,667 --> 00:21:10,000
I picked it up again.

357
00:21:15,800 --> 00:21:16,833
Mom.

358
00:21:18,467 --> 00:21:19,800
Where are you staying now?

359
00:21:20,967 --> 00:21:22,267
A hotel for now.

360
00:21:24,133 --> 00:21:25,267
Mom, I'm sorry.

361
00:21:26,667 --> 00:21:28,467
This is all my fault.

362
00:21:28,600 --> 00:21:29,600
No, my child.

363
00:21:29,733 --> 00:21:31,033
Your dad and I have had
a broken marriage

364
00:21:31,167 --> 00:21:32,767
for a long time.

365
00:21:32,900 --> 00:21:35,367
I should have done this
a long time ago.

366
00:21:37,767 --> 00:21:39,900
Let's just focus on Ashley.

367
00:21:40,033 --> 00:21:43,667
I'm planning to set
a healing mass.

368
00:21:43,833 --> 00:21:45,700
We did that for Jess
and it worked.

369
00:21:45,833 --> 00:21:48,233
So, I'm hoping it will work
the same for Ashley.

370
00:21:48,367 --> 00:21:50,833
I will invite more people
for more prayers.

371
00:21:50,967 --> 00:21:52,833
Let's just do it
at the events place

372
00:21:52,967 --> 00:21:55,267
beside the hospital,
so it's nearby.

373
00:21:57,467 --> 00:21:59,300
Mom, thank you.

374
00:21:59,433 --> 00:22:01,967
I appreciate your concern

375
00:22:02,100 --> 00:22:03,833
- for my child.
- Of course.

376
00:22:06,233 --> 00:22:11,800
There's something that's
really bothering me right now.

377
00:22:11,933 --> 00:22:12,967
What is it?

378
00:22:17,200 --> 00:22:18,633
I need answers, Mom.

379
00:22:20,033 --> 00:22:21,467
During my fight with dad,

380
00:22:22,500 --> 00:22:26,100
he said that there are still
many things I don't know.

381
00:22:27,933 --> 00:22:29,367
Mom, what don't I know?

382
00:22:31,367 --> 00:22:34,867
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

383
00:22:40,967 --> 00:22:42,467
[CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY]

384
00:22:42,600 --> 00:22:43,700
I don't know.

385
00:22:43,833 --> 00:22:46,833
I don't know what your father
is talking about.

386
00:22:46,967 --> 00:22:50,600
You know what, old men like him
like to be poetic.

387
00:22:50,767 --> 00:22:52,533
They try to sound deep but

388
00:22:52,667 --> 00:22:55,300
there's really nothing
behind what they say.

389
00:22:55,433 --> 00:22:57,167
Are you sure, Mom?

390
00:22:57,300 --> 00:22:59,000
Is there no other reason
why he would...

391
00:22:59,133 --> 00:23:01,400
why he'd be this angry at me?

392
00:23:01,533 --> 00:23:03,467
Because it feels like
that's what he was implying.

393
00:23:05,033 --> 00:23:06,533
I'm sure.

394
00:23:06,667 --> 00:23:08,467
I don't know...

395
00:23:10,267 --> 00:23:11,933
what his reason really is

396
00:23:12,067 --> 00:23:15,633
or if that's truly
what he meant.

397
00:23:19,600 --> 00:23:20,733
Anyway, Mom,

398
00:23:20,867 --> 00:23:22,000
it's getting late.

399
00:23:24,167 --> 00:23:25,167
I have to go back to Ashley.

400
00:23:25,300 --> 00:23:26,500
- Yes.
- I'm leaving now.

401
00:23:26,633 --> 00:23:28,500
Okay.

402
00:23:28,633 --> 00:23:30,200
And you, Mom?

403
00:23:30,333 --> 00:23:31,267
I'll stay a bit longer.

404
00:23:31,400 --> 00:23:32,967
I'll finish my coffee first.

405
00:23:33,100 --> 00:23:35,767
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

406
00:23:42,233 --> 00:23:45,167
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

407
00:23:54,433 --> 00:23:55,400
Aldrin?

408
00:23:59,200 --> 00:24:00,300
Aldrin.

409
00:24:03,100 --> 00:24:05,133
I thought we were friends.

410
00:24:05,267 --> 00:24:06,533
I trusted you.

411
00:24:08,033 --> 00:24:11,433
But because of you,
my family fell apart.

412
00:24:11,567 --> 00:24:14,533
What did we ever do to you
for you to destroy us?

413
00:24:18,900 --> 00:24:20,533
Your family did nothing.

414
00:24:22,667 --> 00:24:23,967
But you?

415
00:24:25,733 --> 00:24:27,400
You did.

416
00:24:29,300 --> 00:24:32,533
Remember when I told you Castelo
was my mother's last name?

417
00:24:34,467 --> 00:24:37,600
Now I want you to know
what my father's last name is.

418
00:24:39,567 --> 00:24:41,633
His last name is Belmonte.

419
00:24:43,600 --> 00:24:47,167
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

420
00:24:53,567 --> 00:24:54,633
Belmonte.

421
00:24:55,867 --> 00:24:56,800
Shocked?

422
00:24:58,567 --> 00:24:59,833
Well, that's right.

423
00:25:01,033 --> 00:25:03,200
I am Walter Belmonte's child.

424
00:25:04,900 --> 00:25:06,533
The one who used
to be your lover.

425
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:10,700
- Aldrin, I...
- Let me finish.

426
00:25:12,767 --> 00:25:15,800
My mother died
from heartbreak and pain.

427
00:25:17,667 --> 00:25:19,067
Because of you.

428
00:25:20,133 --> 00:25:22,600
I ended the affair long before
your mother passed away.

429
00:25:22,733 --> 00:25:25,000
And do you think it can just be
erased that easily

430
00:25:25,133 --> 00:25:27,000
just because you decided
to end it?

431
00:25:29,200 --> 00:25:31,500
My entire family was destroyed.

432
00:25:32,767 --> 00:25:35,067
Just because you wanted
to get even with your husband

433
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:36,500
for cheating on you.

434
00:25:43,433 --> 00:25:45,100
And so I thought...

435
00:25:46,467 --> 00:25:48,900
what if I also just get even
with that?

436
00:25:54,300 --> 00:25:56,433
I will destroy

437
00:25:58,033 --> 00:25:59,533
and ruin

438
00:26:00,800 --> 00:26:02,833
your entire family.

439
00:26:06,300 --> 00:26:07,900
Mark my words.

440
00:26:14,900 --> 00:26:16,267
Excuse me.

441
00:26:16,400 --> 00:26:21,000
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

442
00:26:27,100 --> 00:26:29,200
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

443
00:26:29,333 --> 00:26:33,500
It's impossible for Yolly
to own an expensive watch.

444
00:26:33,633 --> 00:26:35,600
Could she have stolen it
from us?

445
00:26:35,733 --> 00:26:38,967
If Yolly stole it,
why would she leave it behind?

446
00:26:39,100 --> 00:26:42,367
The person who burned my house
is the owner of this watch.

447
00:26:44,067 --> 00:26:46,800
Mom, I think it's time
you tell him the truth.

448
00:26:46,933 --> 00:26:48,167
That is your child.

449
00:26:48,300 --> 00:26:51,067
The person I will bring down.

450
00:26:51,200 --> 00:26:52,100
[WHIMPERING]

451
00:26:52,233 --> 00:26:53,933
The truth is...

452
00:26:54,067 --> 00:26:55,333
You're the arsonist!

453
00:26:55,467 --> 00:26:58,333
- How could you?
- You're a monster.

454
00:26:58,467 --> 00:27:00,533
You want your own child
imprisoned?

455
00:27:00,667 --> 00:27:02,633
Because you are not
my real child!

456
00:27:02,767 --> 00:27:05,167
Be thankful that I still cannot
completely destroy you.

457
00:27:05,300 --> 00:27:08,367
You still need to see
how I will destroy your child.

458
00:27:08,500 --> 00:27:10,233
You are Regina's child
by another man.

459
00:27:10,367 --> 00:27:14,433
That's exactly why you don't
deserve anything from me!

460
00:27:14,567 --> 00:27:17,633
Edward is not
an illegitimate child.

461
00:27:17,800 --> 00:27:20,833
He was not the result
of your mother's affair.
